368
00:24:38,190 --> 00:24:39,019
Of course.

369
00:24:44,140 --> 00:24:47,680
You asked us to come here because you have something to tell us, right?

370
00:24:49,519 --> 00:24:50,589
I can’t deal with this anymore.

371
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:52,509
It’s getting out of hand.

372
00:24:53,390 --> 00:24:54,880
I can’t keep Tert under control anymore.

373
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:55,720
What happened?

374
00:24:56,839 --> 00:24:57,920
Tert…

375
00:24:58,650 --> 00:24:59,519
What did he do?

376
00:25:01,339 --> 00:25:04,970
Tert randomly disappeared the other day

377
00:25:06,599 --> 00:25:07,960
so I followed him out.

378
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:11,519
Tert, don’t.

379
00:25:12,059 --> 00:25:12,750
What are you doing?

380
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:14,490
Our son has run away.

381
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:16,640
That’s not our son, Tert.

382
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:18,140
We have to find our son.

383
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:20,140
He’s missing.

384
00:25:20,140 --> 00:25:21,309
We have to find him.

385
00:25:21,880 --> 00:25:23,660
He hasn’t come back home.

386
00:25:24,619 --> 00:25:26,750
Do you know what day it is?

387
00:25:28,619 --> 00:25:29,660
Of course I do.

388
00:25:31,183 --> 00:25:33,647
It’s the day our son went missing.

389
00:25:38,223 --> 00:25:39,776
We have to find our son, Nuan.

390
00:25:40,655 --> 00:25:41,769
Do you understand?

391
00:25:41,887 --> 00:25:43,296
We have to find our son.

392
00:25:43,791 --> 00:25:46,768
Trust me. Our son may have gotten lost.

393
00:25:47,104 --> 00:25:49,519
Trust me.	Please, Nuan.

394
00:25:51,359 --> 00:25:51,839
Tert,

395
00:25:55,711 --> 00:25:58,271
did you kidnap the kids?

396
00:26:00,624 --> 00:26:00,991
The kids?

397
00:26:05,359 --> 00:26:06,990
When I went to stay with my mom,

398
00:26:08,448 --> 00:26:11,200
did you kidnap the kids to our house?

399
00:26:13,584 --> 00:26:14,544
Did you, Tert?

400
00:26:16,751 --> 00:26:17,567
Did you?

401
00:26:20,688 --> 00:26:21,920
Did you, Tert?

402
00:26:25,630 --> 00:26:30,784
I thought that I knew my husband well and that I was capable of taking care of him.

403
00:26:32,048 --> 00:26:33,471
But from that moment on,

404
00:26:34,367 --> 00:26:35,567
I didn’t know who he was anymore.

405
00:26:40,064 --> 00:26:42,895
Since that day, he’s gone missing

406
00:26:43,119 --> 00:26:44,672
and he hasn’t come home.

407
00:26:47,152 --> 00:26:48,607
I don’t know where he is

408
00:26:48,751 --> 00:26:50,271
or what he plans to do.

409
00:26:51,407 --> 00:26:54,928
I don’t know if he killed those kids.

410
00:27:31,359 --> 00:27:32,799
Hello, what’s up?

411
00:27:32,799 --> 00:27:35,423
Jean, are you busy?

412
00:27:35,855 --> 00:27:37,087
Can you come over?

413
00:27:37,807 --> 00:27:40,864
I’m a little busy right now with the café.

414
00:27:41,551 --> 00:27:42,400
Is everything alright?

415
00:27:43,392 --> 00:27:44,688
Will you go to the club with me?

416
00:27:46,144 --> 00:27:47,215
I can’t today.

417
00:27:47,647 --> 00:27:48,751
Can we go tomorrow?

418
00:27:50,349 --> 00:27:51,680
But I really want to see you.

419
00:27:53,150 --> 00:27:56,144
Jean, dinner is ready. Come eat.

420
00:27:56,672 --> 00:27:57,599
Our children are waiting.

421
00:28:09,807 --> 00:28:14,240
You’re married?

422
00:28:45,248 --> 00:28:46,864
All this time you’ve been lying to me, haven’t you?

423
00:28:53,119 --> 00:28:54,160
Did you ever love me?

424
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,008
Yes.

425
00:28:56,096 --> 00:28:57,231
I love you.

426
00:28:58,096 --> 00:29:00,480
If I say I love you, it means I really do.

427
00:29:00,829 --> 00:29:02,319
I really love you, Weir.

428
00:29:02,367 --> 00:29:03,369
Love?

429
00:29:05,743 --> 00:29:07,087
How could it be love when you did this to me?

430
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:09,079
What about your wife and children?

431
00:29:09,503 --> 00:29:10,415
Do you love them at all?

432
00:29:11,440 --> 00:29:14,864
Weir, love comes in many forms.

433
00:29:15,584 --> 00:29:18,655
Feeling you love someone is already love.

434
00:29:18,912 --> 00:29:22,569
You don’t have to love only one person.

435
00:29:22,569 --> 00:29:22,576
You don’t have to love only one person.Stop crafting your sentences.

436
00:29:22,576 --> 00:29:24,384
Stop crafting your sentences.

437
00:29:26,059 --> 00:29:28,144
No matter how beautiful your words are,

438
00:29:29,167 --> 00:29:33,023
this shitty behavior won’t make you look better.

439
00:29:35,019 --> 00:29:41,440
Did you know that I ran away to France and refused to go home because my mom cheated on my dad?

440
00:29:42,496 --> 00:29:45,488
Look at me now. I’m having an affair with someone’s spouse.

441
00:29:47,167 --> 00:29:48,288
It really hurts.

442
00:29:48,384 --> 00:29:49,327
Listen to me.

443
00:29:50,127 --> 00:29:52,352
We love each other, don’t we?

444
00:29:53,231 --> 00:29:55,023
You don’t have to worry about my family.

445
00:29:55,471 --> 00:29:56,640
I’ll handle it.

446
00:29:56,688 --> 00:29:58,256
Jean, we have to break up.

447
00:30:00,736 --> 00:30:01,935
We can’t.

448
00:30:02,223 --> 00:30:04,031
You’re crazy about me.

449
00:30:04,463 --> 00:30:06,029
How can you be such an asshole?

450
00:30:06,784 --> 00:30:07,471
Weir.

451
00:30:08,703 --> 00:30:09,743
I’m an asshole?

452
00:30:09,950 --> 00:30:13,215
You slept around but I didn’t say anything.

453
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:14,496
I was single then.

454
00:30:14,864 --> 00:30:15,855
I was single.

455
00:30:16,528 --> 00:30:18,496
But you can’t live a double life.

456
00:30:20,928 --> 00:30:22,240
Why not?

457
00:30:23,215 --> 00:30:24,784
My dad could.

458
00:30:25,087 --> 00:30:27,392
He shared his love for everyone.

459
00:30:27,680 --> 00:30:28,703
I’m the same.

460
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:32,720
I can share my love for both you and family.

461
00:30:36,240 --> 00:30:40,736
My mom once told me adult relationships are complicated.

462
00:30:43,152 --> 00:30:44,144
I get it now.

463
00:30:45,215 --> 00:30:50,192
I get that it’s just an excuse adults give to children when they want to do something selfish.

464
00:30:51,663 --> 00:30:52,256
Weir.

465
00:31:34,160 --> 00:31:35,248
Did Krating make these?

466
00:31:57,519 --> 00:31:59,056
Your mom’s cookies.

467
00:32:03,119 --> 00:32:05,776
She made some for everyone at the café.

468
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:08,304
Even Mone got a few boxes home.

469
00:32:08,703 --> 00:32:12,688
She made that box specially for you.

470
00:32:15,872 --> 00:32:20,576
Now you know what flavor was missing from the cookies.

471
00:32:22,847 --> 00:32:24,569
It’s your mom’s flavor.

472
00:32:26,928 --> 00:32:29,056
The woman you’ve been avoiding for over ten years.

473
00:32:30,544 --> 00:32:32,539
It’s the flavor of family.

474
00:32:48,624 --> 00:32:50,160
Why did you have to build up drama?

475
00:32:52,432 --> 00:32:54,256
Do you love seeing me cry that much?

476
00:33:00,352 --> 00:33:02,304
I want you to talk things out with your mom.

477
00:33:05,503 --> 00:33:06,096
Chef,

478
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:10,031
you still have your mom, your sister,

479
00:33:10,688 --> 00:33:12,768
and many others who are your family.

480
00:33:20,112 --> 00:33:22,367
and a home to go back to.

481
00:33:24,511 --> 00:33:28,304
No dishes are as delicious as what your mom makes.

482
00:33:28,799 --> 00:33:34,880
Maybe your fear can be overcome with forgiveness.

483
00:33:37,471 --> 00:33:45,248
She made a mistake in the past but she owns up to it and tries her best to fix it.

484
00:33:46,799 --> 00:33:48,223
You should give her a chance.

485
00:33:51,215 --> 00:33:56,064
But there’s someone else who shouldn’t be given another chance to hurt you again.

486
00:34:02,336 --> 00:34:03,392
Who are you talking about?

487
00:34:03,728 --> 00:34:07,759
Before you got home, Jean was waiting for you here

488
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:11,487
so we heard about your fight.

489
00:34:11,552 --> 00:34:12,831
But I sent him away.

490
00:34:13,056 --> 00:34:16,128
More like you begged him to leave.

491
00:34:24,719 --> 00:34:29,824
I’m sorry for troubling you guys again.

492
00:34:31,599 --> 00:34:32,367
It’s alright.

493
00:34:32,784 --> 00:34:37,280
But please remember that people who make amends are different from people who make excuses.

494
00:34:38,351 --> 00:34:41,760
It’s your choice what kind of people you want in your life.

495
00:34:47,072 --> 00:34:47,952
Thank you.

496
00:34:50,271 --> 00:34:51,407
Thank you all.

497
00:34:54,559 --> 00:34:56,000
Where are you going, Chef?

498
00:34:56,784 --> 00:34:58,112
To make desserts, of course.

499
00:34:59,311 --> 00:35:01,231
To make desserts for my family members.

500
00:35:20,576 --> 00:35:24,159
We spoke to Ms. Nuan, Mr.Tert’s wife.

501
00:35:24,911 --> 00:35:28,831
We’re sure he kidnapped Mr. Punn.

502
00:35:29,615 --> 00:35:31,840
Remember the case from 21 years ago I told you about?

503
00:35:32,250 --> 00:35:39,552
One boy was kidnapped and ended up getting killed. It was Mr. Tert’s son.

504
00:35:41,152 --> 00:35:43,615
After he lost his son,

505
00:35:44,016 --> 00:35:46,784
he started suffering from mental illness	and having hallucinations.

506
00:35:47,280 --> 00:35:49,344
He thinks every boy he sees is his son.

507
00:35:51,340 --> 00:35:56,159
I think that’s why Mr. Punn was kidnapped.

508
00:35:57,311 --> 00:36:00,090
Now another scary thing has happened.

509
00:36:00,090 --> 00:36:00,096
Now another scary thing has happened.What is it?

510
00:36:00,096 --> 00:36:01,007
What is it?

511
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:07,056
Mr. Tert relapsed and disappeared from his house.

512
00:36:08,096 --> 00:36:10,880
Ms. Nuan is very worried something bad might happen again.

513
00:36:11,039 --> 00:36:13,407
Why didn’t you guys tell me sooner?

514
00:36:13,679 --> 00:36:14,976
I could have helped you investigate.

515
00:36:17,871 --> 00:36:20,880
Your father and I are in part responsible for his condition.

516
00:36:22,519 --> 00:36:23,903
What do you mean?

517
00:36:28,320 --> 00:36:31,023
He asked us to report the news about his son’s disappearance

518
00:36:31,871 --> 00:36:33,791
hoping it will help him find the boy sooner

519
00:36:34,175 --> 00:36:39,376
but we chose to focus on another news that more people were interested in.

520
00:36:41,103 --> 00:36:43,519
If we hadn’t abandoned Mr. Tert’s case,

521
00:36:44,592 --> 00:36:46,175
this wouldn’t have happened.

522
00:36:47,152 --> 00:36:50,096
No kids would have been kidnapped.

523
00:36:51,900 --> 00:36:58,335
So you didn’t tell me because you were scared I’d be disappointed in you?

524
00:37:00,655 --> 00:37:08,672
We’ve always kept up our appearances and taught you to be a high-principled journalist,

525
00:37:10,992 --> 00:37:15,791
but we have poor journalism ethics ourselves.

526
00:37:15,952 --> 00:37:17,360
We’re ashamed.

527
00:37:18,288 --> 00:37:20,367
That’s why we never told you this story in detail.

528
00:37:23,456 --> 00:37:25,456
Dad, Mom,

529
00:37:27,632 --> 00:37:29,648
I can never be disappointed in you guys,

530
00:37:30,480 --> 00:37:33,503
because what you’re doing right now

531
00:37:33,583 --> 00:37:36,096
is trying to fix your past mistake.

532
00:37:37,423 --> 00:37:40,480
Stop blaming yourselves and let’s fix the problem together.

533
00:37:44,911 --> 00:37:45,440
Thanks.

534
00:37:45,887 --> 00:37:46,447
Thanks.

535
00:37:49,360 --> 00:37:51,023
If the three of us work together,

536
00:37:51,936 --> 00:37:52,864
we will surely be successful.

537
00:38:06,119 --> 00:38:07,807
What’s Meena doing?

538
00:38:10,496 --> 00:38:11,800
Hey, don’t hurt me!

539
00:38:12,768 --> 00:38:14,735
Calm down. I’m your teacher.

540
00:38:16,463 --> 00:38:18,784
You’re in primary grades. What are you doing here?

541
00:38:19,168 --> 00:38:20,016
Mesa.

542
00:38:24,255 --> 00:38:27,103
Sorry I’m late. I had to submit an assignment.

543
00:38:29,648 --> 00:38:31,344
Is something wrong, Mr. Toomtam?

544
00:38:32,128 --> 00:38:35,552
No, I saw her standing alone, so I said hi.

545
00:38:36,096 --> 00:38:39,824
